OL,3,CFormer police officer jailed for
OL,4,Cburglary and corruption
OL,6,FHe claimed he was being blackmailed
OL,7,Fand had committed a burglary after
OL,8,Fbeing "tasked" to do it by an unknown
OL,9,Fperson. He said he had taken the safe
OL,10,Fand had been instructed to leave it on
OL,11,Fwasteland.
OL,13,FThe Hirwaun local said he was being
OL,14,Fblackmailed about a woman he had met
OL,15,Fonline, which suggested the
OL,16,Finvolvement of a Bridgend-based
OL,17,Forganised crime group.
OL,19,FAccording to Cooke, he was being
OL,20,Fblackmailed over sexual pictures he
OL,21,Fhad sent of himself.
